Super agent, Mino Raiola, has died at the age of 54 after battling with illness, the UK Mirror reports. Raiola represented footballers like Paul Pogba of Manchester United and Borussia Dortmund’s Erling Haaland. The Dutchman had been in hospital for minor surgery, though not much detail was given. It may be that this was more serious than initially reported, with the sad news coming through today that the agent has passed away after an unspecified illness. More to follow…